Class Package

  • java.lang.Object
    • Package

  • public class Package
extends java.lang.Object
    A class representing packages that can be placed in a cargo space. It contains all the needed information to know what part of the space a package occupies and the methods to manipulate a package (e.g. by rotating it).

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      Package(java.lang.String type)
      A constructor that constructs a package with certain values according to the definition of the six available pre-defined package types (A, B, C, L, P, T) or the data stored temporarily in the static arrays that store information about new package types..
      Package(java.lang.String type, int length, int width, int height, double value)
      A constructor that creates a package with a given type/name, length, width, height and value.

      • Package

        public Package(java.lang.String type,
               int length,
               int width,
               int height,
               double value)
        A constructor that creates a package with a given type/name, length, width, height and value. That information is stored in several static arrays so that a package of the same type can later be created without completely defining it new.

    • Method Detail

      • setPackage

        public void setPackage(java.lang.String type)
        This method sets the shape of a package (the coordinates it occupies in the cargo space). The number and values of the stored coordinates depend on the dimensions of the package. Alternatively (for the pentomino-shaped packages) an array holding the coordinates occupied by the package is accessed to create the package.
        Parameters:
        type - The desired type of package.

      • setRotations

        public void setRotations(int state)
        A different method of rotating a package. It uses the fact that there are a certain number of states in which a package can be rotated. The index of that state determines how the package will be rotated.
        Parameters:
        state - The index designating a certain rotation state of the package.
